caption: b"The submission period for the CSCEC Photography Contest of #WitnessHappiness only has 3 days left.:sparkles: All CSCECers, CSCEC fans, and photograph fans worldwide are welcome! You can win a lot of prizes. And your works may have the opportunity to be displayed on our social media platform. Don't wait, come and join us. :light_bulb:Link in bio"

b"#WitnessHappiness Did you know in Singapore, 1 in 25 people live in a home built by CSCEC Singapore?
Welcome to Singapore on CSCEC\xe2\x80\x99s #WitnessHappiness Cloud Open Day! Today, we will have a close look at CSCEC\xe2\x80\x99s largest industrial project in Singapore: the Bulim Square project at Jurong Innovation District (JID). Covering an area of 400,000 square metres, the square will become the first landmark at JID.  Smart technologies, such as Building Information Modeling (BIM) and Integrated Digital Delivery (IDD) are being used in the project. During the epidemic, the project actively improved the living conditions of workers through a series of measures, including the construction of workers' dormitories.

What kind of sparks will be generated when the Jurong Innovation Zone encounters CSCEC Singapore? Follow our BIM manager Rob to explore what's happening in one of our on-going mega projects. #CSCEC #project #construction #technology #openday"

b"#cscecproject Dubai is at the forefront of smart communication. Recently, the Dubai Intelligent Transportation Center, which was jointly constructed by @cscec_middleeast, was officially opened. It is currently one of the world's largest integrated traffic control platform management centers with the most advanced intelligent system technology. The intelligent transportation system of the center undertakes the functions of comprehensive transportation management, effectively applying information technology, data communication transmission technology, electronic sensing technology, etc. During its operation, the coverage of ITS roads in Dubai city will increase from the current 11% to 60%, so as to accurately predict and manage traffic flow and quickly formulate emergency plans. \nIn the future, CSCEC will continue to built and witness a better life with its professional and technological ability. \n#CSCEC #Dubai #traffic #construction"

b'Two high-rise architectures constructed by CSCEC won #Emporis Skyscraper Awards!  Recently, the #Emporis announced that ten buildings from around the world won the prize, among them Beijing Leeza SOHO and Tianjin Chow Tai Fook Center made the list. 

Located in southwest Beijing, Leeza SOHO is a masterpiece by the architectural legend Zaha Hadid, which perfectly achieves the perfect combination of architecture, technology, art and ingenuity. Straddling by a subway service tunnel, the tower\xe2\x80\x99s design divides its volume into two halves enclosed by a single facade shell, creating the world\xe2\x80\x99s tallest atrium at 200m. This rotation of the atrium intertwines Leeza SOHO\xe2\x80\x99s two halves in a dynamic \xe2\x80\x98pas de deux\xe2\x80\x99.

Previously, it was awarded the 2018 "World's Top 10 Most Beautiful Buildings" for its world-class design and construction difficulty, Archdaily\xe2\x80\x99s "Most Anticipated Building" in 2019 and the Best Tall Building 200-299 meters 2020 Award of Excellence.

Two high-rise architectures constructed by CSCEC won the w Tai Fook Center, the tallest building in northern China. #Skyscraper #cscec'

b'Han Dynasty was a prosperous dynasty of ancient China. Han Culture Expo Park built by CSCEC is located at Shaanxi and perfectly presents #HanDynasty. Today, let us travel back in time and feel the unique charm of the Han Dynasty . #WitnessHappiness'

Submissions of works refer to the following four categories: #ExtraordinaryStructure #ArchitectureInteraction #CSCECSite #CSCECPower

b'Chinese traditional architecture not only shows superb skill, but also profound aesthetic meaning.\nRecently, China\xe2\x80\x99s largest complex of ancient buildings in a courtyard-like imitation of the Song Dynasty, the Avalokitesvara Dharmadhatu Zhengfa\xc2\xa0Lecture\xc2\xa0Temple project, officially passed the completion acceptance. The project team drew inspiration from the ancient Chinese mortise and tenon technique, gorgeously combining the wood decorations and concrete beams. With ingenuity, CSCECers built the pure wooden architecture, by hand-polishing beams and columns with a DBH of more than one meter.\nInheriting traditional construction concepts and techniques, CSCEC will continue to devote itself to the development of more poetic living aesthetics.'

b'Do you know that Hong Kong also has a \xe2\x80\x9cForbidden City Museum\xe2\x80\x9d?\nOn November 18, Hong Kong Palace Museum built by China State Construction Engineering (Hong Kong) Limited, a subsidiary of China State Construction held the completion ceremony for its building structure. \nHong Kong Palace Museum combines Hong Kong\xe2\x80\x99s contemporary urban culture with Chinese traditional visual art culture and spatial culture, which not only presents the fascination of traditional Chinese culture, but also reflects the unique city style of Hong Kong. The project is expected to be completed by the end of 2021 and open to the public in 2022, which will bring brand new artistic and cultural experience to Hong Kong citizens and its tourists. #museum#chineseart'

b'#WitnessHappiness  Do you want to know how prosperous the Han Dynasty was 2000 years ago? Have you ever wondered about the ingenuity of ancient Chinese architectural structures? This time, the #WitnessHappiness cloud open day will go to Hanzhong, Shaanxi where #CSCEC has built a Han Culture Expo Park, with a total area of 153,800 square meters, to perfectly present the culture and architectural decorative style of the Han Dynasty. Now, follow our expositor to witness the construction stories of this magnificent palace, trace back Han history and experience Han culture together. #cloudopenday'

b'Green construction technology to build a modern campus. The China-Singapore Tianjin Eco-City 12-year School project, contracted by CSCEC, was recently awarded the \xe2\x80\x9cLeadership in Sustainable Design and Performance Award\xe2\x80\x9d in the \xe2\x80\x9cAsia-Pacific Leadership in Green Building Award 2020" by World Green Building Council.

The campus located in the Binhai Tourist area of Tianjin has a total construction area of 53,600 square meters. Adhering to the people-oriented design concept, the project team adopted green construction technology to create a safe and durable, resource-saving and livable modern campus. Let\xe2\x80\x99s take a look: 
:white_heavy_check_mark: Multi-functional roof landscape: the concept of urban agriculture is introduced to the roof, as seen by the roof garden made on the building.
:white_heavy_check_mark: Solar panels on the roof of the natatorium\xef\xbc\x9athe panels can improve the efficiency of renewable energy.
:white_heavy_check_mark: The curtain wall is made of materials with strong thermal insulation performance, effectively reducing the heat radiation by more than 30%.
:white_heavy_check_mark: Indoor light: full use of natural lighting and intelligent lighting control system for differential lighting, to achieve energy conservation.
#construction #ecofriendly #greentech #cscec'

b':sparkles:For the Chengdu Museum project, the surface is covered by brass, presenting a unique appearance of "gold inlaid with jade". :man_construction_worker_selector: With a total construction area of approximately 65,000 square meters and a collection of more than 200,000 cultural relics, it is the largest museum in southwest China and the largest shadow puppet museum in the world. At the same time, taking into account the protection of historical culture and relics according to local conditions, the design of the museum adopts a full-system seismic design.'

b"#CSCECNews Recently, the 3.4-kilometer-long Longyan Bridge in China\xe2\x80\x99s Fujian Province, constructed by CSCEC, opened to traffic. It is the world's first cable-stayed bridge that uses horizontal double rotations technology. Due to the fact the bridge is adjacent to the river, existing roads, and railway lines, a great challenge to the construction was posed. The project team, firstly, rotated the main tower to the predetermined position. After that, the tower and the girder synchronously were rotated to the designed position as a whole. The maximum bearing capacity of the sliding blocks used in the rotation process is up to 25,000 tons, equivalent to the weight of 2.5 Eiffel Towers. The bridge will speed up Longyan's integrated construction. #bridge #construction"

b"Recently, CSCEC has transformed and upgraded Xi'an's old communities with professional customized services which has helped the old residential area regain its luster.\nIn the tailor-made plan, residential corridors are equipped with sensor lights, and sidewalks are encrypted with additional street lights to facilitate residents' night travel. Combining modern technologies such as cloud computing and big data, and introducing intelligent facial recognition access control system and other devices, the old residential area has been transformed into a smart community. In addition to this, the old community also has a smooth spacious road, lush green plants and rich entertainment facilities.\nAfter the unremitting efforts of the project team, the trivial problems of the residents were properly resolved. The appearance of the community has been enhanced, the function of the houses has been advanced, the infrastructure has been renovated, and the living environment has been improved. Consequently, the buildings and communities shaped by reinforced concrete is filled with an atmosphere of warmth and happiness."

b'"Zhengzhou Olympic Sports Center", Zhengzhou City, Henan Province \n:sparkles::sparkles::sparkles:\nThe Zhengzhou Olympic Sports Center, jointly undertaken by CSCEC Southwest Design Institute and CSCEC Eighth Engineering Bureau, provides a place for the people of Zhengzhou to watch sports events. The overall design concept of the Zhengzhou Olympic Sports Center is derived from the meaning of "Heaven, Earth, and the Yellow River ", it adopts the "Pin" pattern, takes the east-west direction as the main axis, and forms a north-south symmetrical layout. The stadium, gymnasium, and swimming pool are like three stone islands in the Yellow River. The surrounding environment looks like the water of the Yellow River, reflecting the profound historical and cultural heritage of Zhengzhou.:building_construction:'

b'Recently, an inauguration and handover ceremony of the Public Engineering Technology School was held in the province of Djelfa, Algeria. The institute was designed and built by CSCEC. It covers an area of five hectares, including teaching building, laboratory building, dormitory building, football field and operation practice base. #Algeria #construction #engineering #civilengineering'

b'#CSCECNews Recently, the right side of the Pocitelli Tunnel, the first bid section of the Bosnia-Herzegovina Pan-European 5C Corridor Highway, successfully penetrated. The Pocitelli tunnel is about 1,170 meters long. Ensuring the health of employees, the project team completed the penetration node 4 months ahead of the original plan in an orderly and efficient manner, through scientific and effective prevention.\n:man_construction_worker_selector:\nIn the future, CSCEC will continue to provide more and better construction services efficiently under the principle of safety first.'

b'After the outbreak, Antony Berlioz, the senior WSH Coordinator security coordinator of @cscec_singapore , is busier than ever. He volunteered as a dormitory operator for the Punggol North C1&C2 project, taking care of the migrant workers both physically and mentally.

It wasn\xe2\x80\x99t an easy job. He worked day and night and tried his best to look after our colleagues. In addition to his own job, he also coordinated with the local organizations to support all workers, making sure that everyone got the things they needed.

Here at CSCEC, there are still many CSCECers like Antony who have stayed on duty during the epidemic. Many thanks for their perseverance and kind help. We firmly believe that as long as we work together, we will overcome the challenges and difficulties. #CSCECerPower #CSCEC #teamwork'

b'Haritha is a CSCECer from Sri Lanka, who not only participated in the construction of Sri Lanka Southern Expressway Extension Project undertaken by CSCEC, but also personally experienced the changes brought by the project.\nWhen he drives home on the Southern Expressway and recalls the village road in his childhood and the winding road in his youth, he has truly felt that though the distance back home gets further and further, the completion of the expressway has greatly reduced the time spent on the road. Not only Haritha, people from all walks in life are all also witnessing the convenience brought to this country by this long awaited highway. #SriLanka #expressway #expressways #highway #'

b'On October. 21, #CSCEC Singapore was honored to receive numerous awards at the Land Transport Authority Annual SHE Award Convention, including the Construction Safety Excellence Award, the Workplace Health Award, etc. \nVideo Source: LTA'

b'#CSCECNews Recently, Prince Tea Banh, Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Defense of Cambodia, and Wang Wentian, Chinese Ambassador to Cambodia inspected the China-aid Project of Morodok Techo National Stadium. They listened to the report of the project overview and the progress of on-site construction, etc. In addition, they went to the construction site to get a better understanding of the progress of the project. Prince Tea Banh said that the stadium is a key project in Cambodia, one which he hopes will be transformed into a high-quality project and landmark building by CSCEC.
:building_construction:
China-aid Project of Morodok Techo National Stadium, located in the north of Phnom Penh, is a large stadium with a seating capacity of 60000 spectators. Personally selected by Cambodian prime minister Hun Sen, the overall design resembles a sailboat, spectacular and gorgeous. After completion, it will serve as the main venue for the 2023 Southeast Asian Games.
#CSCEC #Cambodia #Stadium #sports'

b'#CSCECNews China State Construction Engineering Corporation (CSCEC) launched English version of "CSCEC 2020 Interim Report" on October 15. As a company listed only on China A shares market, CSCEC released the English Interim Report on its own initiative, which not only shows its corporate image of globalization and keeps pace with the internationalization of the capital market, but also shows its confidence in internal control and corporate governance.\nIn the future, CSCEC will constantly benchmark itself against world-class companies and industry-leading companies and continuously improve its strength as a listed company. It will also increase its efforts on overseas promotion and dissemination activities in line with the needs of global investors. Specifically, CSCEC will release more and more corporate announcements, regular reports and promotional materials in English through overseas media matrixes including the English official website and social media, in a bid to enhance the pertinence and effectiveness of information disclosure, strengthen communication and exchanges with global investors, allow more investors to get knowledge of CSCEC and demonstrate CSCEC\'s investment potential and value.\nTo read English version of CSCEC 2020 Interim Report: https://english.cscec.com/tzgx/reports/'

b"Xi'an Daming Palace Danfengmen Site Museum, Xi\xe2\x80\x99an City, Shanxi Province\nDaming Palace was built in the Tang Dynasty and has a history of more than 1,300 years. #CSCEC has rebuilt the Palace on its relics and its cultural heritage remains an extremely important reference for us to study the history of the Tang Dynasty.#xian #museum"

b'In this new episode of #ThenVSNow series, we will show you the Hong Kong-Zhuhai-Macao Bridge. \nThen: Before the Hong Kong \xe2\x80\x93 Zhuhai \xe2\x80\x93 Macao Bridge was completed, it took about 4 hours to drive from Hong Kong to Zhuhai and Macao. \nNow: Situated at the waters of Lingdingyang of Pearl River Estuary, the Hong Kong \xe2\x80\x93 Zhuhai \xe2\x80\x93 Macao Bridge co-constructed by CSCEC is a mega-size sea crossing bridge that connects Hong Kong to Macau and Zhuhai City of Guangdong Province. The bridge opened to the public on October 24, 2018, and it reduced the travel time among these three places to about 40 minutes. #bridge #construction #bridge construction #constructionengineer'

b'The 2022 Winter Olympic Complex Training Center aka the Ice Altar has been completed after three years\xe2\x80\x99 construction by CSCEC. It is the first completed venue for the 2022 Beijing Winter Olympic Games. Besides the Ice Altar, CSCEC has also undertaken the construction of other 2022 Winter Olympic Projects. Let\xe2\x80\x99s look forward to coming of the 2022 Winter Olympic Games together.  #winterolympics2022 #winterolympics #winterolympicgames #construction #constructionengineering'

b'Can you imagine what the future classroom will look like? CSCEC completed a \xe2\x80\x9cfuture classroom\xe2\x80\x9d with a construction area of 310 square meters in just ten days by using modular construction technology.\nThe entire building space of the future classroom presents an "X"-shaped layout. Each unit module is a complete space. The spaces are open and connected to each other. More standard box unit modules can be added infinitely, and more space combinations can be expanded. In this independent and shared space, teaching activities can be integrated with the surrounding community, integrate learning into life, and stimulate unlimited creativity.\n#CSCEC #future #school #creativity #community'

b'The first Monday in October is designated as World Architecture Day. This year, let us move toward a better urban future through architecture.
The Oasis Terraces project undertaken by @cscec_singapore is the largest construction project in Singapore's new-generation large-scale neighborhood center plan. It won the HDB Design Awards 2019 and the BCA Construction Excellence Award 2020.
Here, the Oasis terrace is connected to the waterway, and people can experience nature near public facilities such as neighborhood shopping malls. The gentle slope of the building extends the role of the park to the community center. It is also a gardening project that brings residents together to plant and maintain them, and has become a link connecting community residents. 160,000 residents living in Punggol have benefited from its construction.
Integrating shopping, leisure, catering, fitness, medical treatment and training, the sky garden not only allowed the community residents to enjoy the convenience of life, but also feel the living environment of "a garden".
#CSCEC #Singapore #garden #worldarchitectureday #architecture'

b'Zhangjiajie Grand Canyon Glass Bridge", Zhangjiajie City, Hunan Province\nZhangjiajie Grand Canyon Glass Bridge is a project jointly completed by designer Haim Dotan and  CSCEC, also known as \xe2\x80\x9cYuntiandu\xe2\x80\x9d. Although the meaning of this bridge is to connect two mountains, because Yuntiandu uses transparent glass material, visitors can better overlook the entire Zhangjiajie Grand Canyon on the glass bridge. Climbing on this bridge in the morning when the weather is clear makes it feel even more like you are in the clouds and you can touch the blue sky with your hands.'

b'Falling on the 15th day of the eighth lunar month, the Mid-Autumn Festival, also called the Moon Festival is another important traditional occasion to reunite with family and friends, aside from the Spring Festival.:full_moon:

In Chinese culture, a full moon symbolizes reunion. It is a day for families to appreciate the moon together, enjoy moon cakes :moon_cake:and make lanterns :red_paper_lantern:with blessings and wishes on them together. 

On the occasion of this special day, no matter where you are, CSCEC wishes you and your family a day filled with happiness, love, good health and companionship. #happymidautumnfestival #cscec'

b'#CSCECProject The Suvarnabhumi Airport Development Project, contracted by CSCEC, is a major landmark livelihood infrastructure project in Thailand. Since it began construction in 2018, the project has been progressing at a high speed. At present, over 95% of the project has been completed and is scheduled to be completed within this year and put into use next year.
During the epidemic, In order to ensure the health and safety of employees, CSCEC implemented effective measures, such as establishing health records online and separating construction in different areas.
In addition, the rainy season brought invisible pressure to the construction period and safety on site. Through In-depth scientific research of CSCECers, the pipelined operation of the fixed personnel was performed at this point. It not only guaranteed the quality but also improved the efficiency.
Otherwise, the whole project has more than15000 Thai CSCECers. Moreover materials and equipment needed for the construction of the new terminal building, including concrete, steel bars, steel structures and decoration materials, were purchased in Thailand to inject vitality into the local market.

#socialresponsibility #Thailand #Suvarnabhumi #airport #CSCEC'

b'If you meet Ali for the first time at the construction site of the Era Duta North Project of CSCEC Malaysia, you will be impressed that he can speak multiple languages. Ali, who is from Pakistan, joined CSCEC in March 2018 as a mechanic. In addition to English, he can also speak Chinese, Malay, Bengali, Nepali, and other languages, and he learned them all by himself.

Almost everyone on the project knows about him. He is not only good at repairing tower cranes and elevators but also often studies about other machinery repairs on the construction site during his spare time. \xe2\x80\x9cAli has taken a large load off of me since he\xe2\x80\x99s been here. He can handle emergencies on his own.\xe2\x80\x9dhis tutor Zhang Yanfei commented.

Ali has a dream that after accumulating certain savings and mastering better technical skills he can go back to his hometown and build a school for the local kids. The experience of working at CSCEC has made him feel closer to his dream.'

b'In this #WitnessHappiness Cloud Open Day Activity, we will take you to CSCEC Sri Lanka. In Sri Lanka, CSCEC has constructed projects in various sectors such as expressways, hotels, shopping malls, apartments and water conservancy projects. In pushing forward projects construction, CSCEC has always shared advanced technology, protected the environment, employed local residents, and guaranteed CSCECers\xe2\x80\x99 safety. CSCEC has always insisted on common development with local communities, co-founding nursing home with local government, subsidizing schools and hospitals, and carrying out free clinic activities and other charities. \nClick the video to learn more about how CSCEC constructed the projects, fulfilled the social responsibility, and realized win-win cooperation with Sri Lanka. #socialresponsibility #srilanka #hotels #wedding'

b'"Chongqing International Expo Center", Chongqing City\nChongqing International Expo Center has hosted many different activities and conferences, including art exhibitions, cultural exchanges, technological innovation, and other activities. #CSCEC took three years to integrate it into the exhibition park. Can you tell what shape it is? Viewed from a high altitude, the Chongqing National Expo Center is like a butterfly resting on the banks of the Jialing River, which also symbolizes the metamorphosis and take-off of #chongqing \'s exhibition economy.'

b'Recently, the new headquarters project of Commercial Bank of Ethiopia constructed by CSCEC has successfully completed the closure of the curtain walls of the main tower and put on its \xe2\x80\x9cdiamond coat.\xe2\x80\x9d\n\nThe project, located in the business district of the capital Addis Ababa, has total construction area of 160,000 square meters and a tower facade decoration height of 209.15 meters. Once completed, the project will inject great power into the economic development of Ethiopia. #construction #bank #skycraper #cscec #engineering #project #Ethiopia'

b'Here is the #ThenVSNow series. In this episode we are going to visit the Dubai Hassyan Clean Coal Power Plant Project.
 
:right_arrow_selector:Then: In January 2017, to meet the energy needs of the Dubai World Expo, construction of the Hasyan Clean Coal Power Plant in Dubai broke ground along the Persian Gulf. At that time, you could see the vast sand under the burning sun.
 
:right_arrow_selector:Now: Three years in the making, this Clean Coal Power Plant, with more than 120 individual plants, stands out amid the blue sea and sky. On the basis of scientific management to ensure the health and safety of CSCECers, the project team welcomed an important node that successfully connect Unit 1 to the grid, during the epidemic.
 
When completed, the Hasyan project will reduce electricity costs for local residents and businesses and provide strong energy support for the local community.
 
#CSCEC #Dubai #cleanpower #construction'

b'In 2019, Farah Royyana graduated from Zhengzhou University in China, and joined the BSD Phase One Project as a budgeter in CSCEC Indonesia. In 2020, she was awarded excellent new employee for her diligent and responsible work. 

In Indonesia, the construction industry is dominated by men, while Farah still chooses this career, proving to everyone that women shouldn\xe2\x80\x99t be limited and can make contributions in any field. During the one year in CSCEC Indonesia, she took the initiative to work, actively overcame difficulties and helped each other with colleagues. She said that the company offered her opportunities to participate in the whole project circle and learn new knowledge, making her feel the personal growth and value in a team. In the face of the epidemic, she helped translate the epidemic prevention regulations and contribute to ensuring CSCECers\xe2\x80\x99 health and safety. 

Farah is very comfortable with her current life, and always says she is a happy architecture girl. She regards it a blessing to be able to pursue her dream. #womeninbusiness #construction #constructionlife #constructionengineering #womencareer'

b'The construction project of bridges 1 to 5 in Hulhumal\xc3\xa9 has been delivered successfully on September 2. The bridge is an important channel connecting the two artificial islands in Hulhumal\xc3\xa9 and has the integrated functions of transportation and sightseeing. The successful completion of the project greatly facilitates the travel of locals and tourists.\n \nDuring the construction process, although our team of #CSCEC Maldives has gone through challenges such as technical problems, high-temperature environments and epidemic prevention. The construction was carried out smoothly and completed as planned by the joint efforts of the entire team. #CSCECProject'

b'There are many Egyptian workers among the 2,000 employees at the new Capital CBD project in Egypt, where they have gained personal growth and realized self-value. In the last video of CSCEC Egypt\xe2\x80\x99s Cloud Open Day, let\xe2\x80\x99s meet our three colleagues and listen to their stories with CSCEC.

Mr. Najim has forged a deep friendship with many colleagues from different places because of his work. Ms. Hanan, who joined CSCEC at the age of 22, has been with the company for more than 30 years. "This will be my first job after my graduation and it will be my last job ever", she said. There is also Mary from the design department. Influenced by her family, she has been fond of Chinese culture when she was a little girl. After joining CSCEC, she often volunteered at the Free Egypt Experimental School, which was also built by CSCEC, and was happy to see the children get the opportunity for cultural interaction.

#WitnessHappiness and light up the future. The Egyptian and Chinese partners are one big family, working together with unremitting efforts for the construction of the new capital CBD project in Egypt and outline the blueprints for the future of the new Egyptian capital. #CSCECOpenDay #WorldKaleidoscope'

b'"Dingshan Yangtze River Bridge", Chongqing City \nA bridge not only connects people on both sides of one place, but is also an important passage between the two cities. The completion of the Dingshan Yangtze River Bridge has brought convenience to the road from Chongqing to Chengdu and reduced the time people spend on the road. During the construction process, the wind direction and water velocity changed frequently, which brought difficulties to the completion of the project. After four years, the employees of CSCEC Engineering Group finally overcame all the difficulties surrounding the project and completed it, creating a beautiful landscape across the Yangtze River.\n#bridgephotography #constructionengineering #constructionmachinery ##bridge #cscec'

b'#WitnessHappiness Cloud Open Day of @cscecegypt_ins continues! Today, we are visiting the Iconic Tower of the new capital CBD project. After completion, it will reach a height of 385.8 meters and a total of 80 floors. Now it has reached the 40th floor.
During the construction of the Iconic Tower, Chinese and Egyptian partners made concerted efforts and set a number of construction records in the history of Egyptian architecture: the casting of 18,500m\xc2\xb3 of raft foundation, which was planned to be completed in 72 hours, was completed in only 38 hours ahead of schedule. At the same time, the maximum concrete casting volume per hour during peak period was 785m\xc2\xb3/h. In addition, the advanced "Building Machine" technology has also been implemented by the Iconic Tower project in Egypt for the first time.
Next time, the open day of CBD project will continue. We will listen to the stories of the builders here.
#WorldKaleisdoscope'

b"#CSCECInAction CSCEC Cote d 'Ivoire has formulated strict work plans and emergency plans for the safe resumption of work. \nThe forth bridge of Abidjan project team not only made personal protection guidelines in French, but also organized daily temperature checks and group learning on prevention knowledge for CSCECers before work every day. Of course, disinfection and sterilization, epidemic prevention materials, access management of external personnel were also indispensable. At present, the production capacity of the project has basically returned to the previous level.\nLet us continue to contribute and bear witness to the economic recovery and development of Cote d 'Ivoire."

b'#WitnessHappiness at the new wonder of Egypt. The highly expected Cloud Open Day of CSCEC Egypt begins! Please follow our Egyptian CSCECers to start this exploration tour of the new capital CBD project.\nUndertaken by CSCEC, Egypt\xe2\x80\x99s new capital CBD project is also known as the pyramid of the new age. What is so special about the project that earned it this title? What measures the project has taken to ensure the health and safety of our partners? Click the video to find out the answers!\nIn the next episode, we\xe2\x80\x99ll unveil the challenges we faced and the technologies we used in the project. Please look forward to it with us. #WorldKaleisdoscope'

b'#WitnessHappiness One Day to go! On September 3, the \xe2\x80\x9cCSCEC Cloud Open Day\xe2\x80\x9d activities will be officially held at the @cscecegypt_ins new capital CBD project. Please follow our cameras to witness the rise of a new capital in the desert. \nFor more than 30 years, CSCEC Egypt has made continuous efforts to contribute to Egyptian economic development, focus on its public interest, and expand a happy living environment for the Egyptian people.\nPlease stay tuned on CSCEC\xe2\x80\x99s social platforms as we take you into the new capital CBD project in stages. #worldkaleidoscope'

b'#WitnessHappiness The first stop of the \xe2\x80\x9cCSCEC Open Day\xe2\x80\x9d will be launched soon at the @cscecegypt_ins new capital CBD project, located 60km east of Cairo in Egypt. What kind of super-high-rise construction technologies have been involved in building the iconic tower, which will be a landmark of the CBD and of #Egypt after completion? What unforgettable stories have unfolded between Chinese and Egyptian builders during its construction? And during the epidemic, which premise of strict prevention measures have been implemented to ensure the efficient progress of the project? Follow your curiosity, join us to learn more about the project from 360 degrees, and witness happiness together on September 3 during the cloud open day. Please stay tuned! #CSCECOpenday #WorldKaleidoscope #CBD #africa'

b'Chengdu Dong\xe2\x80\x99anhu Sports Park, the main stadium of the 2021 World University Games, was built with the participation of the CSCEC. The top of the stadium is made up of 12,540 pieces of glazed glass that form a "Sun and Immortal birds" pattern and took 80 days to complete.

Because the opening ceremony is held at night, the main stadium will achieve the natural effect of light and shadow, so that the \xe2\x80\x9cSun and Immortal birds\xe2\x80\x9d pattern can be seen without the steel structure by day and without the shapes of lights at night. b'Five bridges dance \xe2\x80\x9cballet\xe2\x80\x9d in the air and set the world records. \nOn August 21st, at the Chongqing Expressway Project constructed by CSCEC, five bridge sections were successfully rotated into position to form an overpass. b'CSCEC wishes you good fortune on the Chinese New Year\xef\xbc\x81#happychinesenewyear #yearoftherat #cscec'

b'As the most important and celebrated festival in China, the eve of the Chinese New Year is just coming! Let\xe2\x80\x99s have a glimpse of how our CSCECers around the world embrace and celebrate the coming Year of the Rat in diverse and special ways. \nCSCECers in Egypt have decorated the #CSCEC home in traditional Chinese ways. And those in the Middle East and Algeria have invited their local friends to enjoy dumplings and other Chinese gourmet dishes. Some of them have shared their wishes for the coming year through the lens. \xe2\x80\x9cWherever we are, togetherness is our home.\xe2\x80\x9d All CSCECers around the world accompany each other and celebrate the Chinese New Year together in #CSCEC family. #reunion #bestwishes #yearofrat #2020chinesenewyear #WorldKaleidoscope'

b'\xe2\x80\x9cEat, drink and be merry\xe2\x80\x9d. Gourmet food is a must-have for festival celebrations. The reunion dinner during the Chinese New Year is an annual feast and is often considered the most important meal of the entire year.

As with Chinese New Year activities and decorations, CSCECers from all corners of the world share the traditional Chinese dishes with blessings for the next year. Dumplings represent reunion and good fortune. While wrapping dumplings, people wrap their best wishes inside. Spring rolls, as the name implies, are eaten to celebrate the coming spring. Fish symbolizes surplus and wealth. By eating fish, we wish to have prosperity in the new year.

Being accompanied by delicate food, we get together to celebrate the new year with our #cscec family and enjoy the flavor of reunion. #springfestival #lunarnewyear #familymeal'

b'Chinese New Year, also known as Chinese Spring Festival, is the most important festival in China. It is a time for family reunion and yearning for future. Celebrating the festival at home is the happiest time of the year, and preparing for the celebration at home is the prelude to the happiness. \nThe Chinese character \xe2\x80\x9cFu\xe2\x80\x9d \xef\xbc\x88meaning good luck\xef\xbc\x89and poetic couplets are pasted to the sides of doors and walls to bring in good fortune. Red lanterns are hung up on trees to ward off bad luck. Accompanied by each other, #CSCECers from all over the world are preparing for the celebration at our #CSCEC homes. #ChineseNewYear #SpringFestival #customs #tradition #celebration'
